Payments (Main Category)
-> ENP(EposNow) integration (sub category)
Troubleshooting Steps

Question: Are you on Windows; Android; Apple device?
Question: Are you setting up to the till or Saturn is your portal till?
Step 1: Open up service account or remote into till or login to backoffice : eposnowhq.com -> setup-> payments- terminal setup & assign store location to ENP( saturn, Air ; P400) { If  setup in back end errors check location, under setup - location - location, and make sure everything is setup.}
Step 2: Cloud sync the till (3 lines -> cloud sync.)
Step 3: Settings-> payments -> eposnow payments -> enable it( if customer has more than one ENP, have them select the blue button that says change and they select the ENP that they want associated with the till.)
Step 4: Turn on the ENP and go through the setup process of the hardware itself.
Step 5: How to switch ENP to Cellular Data? :  Settings (Air & Saturn) ->network & Internet -> cellular data -> check to see if it says active -> press the back arrow , go to WiFi and turn it off. If the cellular data doesn't start once you do, that simple power cycle of the ENP should connect you to 4G/5G network depending on your region.
Additional information: if customer wants to disable receipts or tips : settings -> payments -> eposnow payments.

Note:  If a customer is using an Apple IOS product, and can't see Epos Now Payments options, they will need to reach out to Apple as their IOS firewall is blocking cloud service to Epos Now.

backoffice : eposnowhq.com -> setup-> payments->payments set-up -> log back in ( if you don't have MFA setup. Make sure to select the correct region flag, add your phone number,  select codes to be sent to SMS. Save.  Log out & back in.)-> scroll to bottom and enable additional card types. ( This is also where you can change to/ from faster payouts or change your cut off time. Cut off time takes into effect after 24 hrs if you change it.)
