-> PDQ(Third Party) integration (sub category)
Troubleshooting Steps
Step 1: Open up service account or (till)3 lines -> App store -> Myapp or login ( eposnowhq.com) to backoffice-> app store-> my app-> locate third party PDQ( Teya, Take Payments, Dejavoo, Lloyd Cardnet(a.k.a. Castle PDQ, etc.)->  select setup & put in the information provided by the MP PDQ.
Step 2: Cloud sync the till (3 lines -> cloud sync.)
Step 3: Settings-> payments -> third party PDQ provider-> enable it( if customer has more than one PDQ, have them select the blue button that says change and they select the PDQ that they want associated with the till.)
Step 4: Turn on the PDQ and go through the setup process of the hardware itself.
Additional information: if a customer wants to disable receipts: settings -> payments -> Dejavoo or if it's another  provider they have to reach out to their MP (Merchant Processor).

We are no longer partners with global payment( evo/ heartland) & paymentsense (dojo). 


