->  Standalone (sub category)
Troubleshooting Steps
Depending on customer setup the standalone tender type button can be one of the main tenders on the screen or under the keypad, under the more options with 3 dots. This is located in the area after you hit pay.( eposnowhq.com) back office -> setup->tender

Explanation to why it happens? : If one or both devices are on wifi. The card reader will always have better connectivity( due to having cellular data.) . If the customer has either and the card reader on wifi and getting transactions not showing on the till. It means the POS system missed the transaction frequency length, when ENP was sending the data back. Always best to have ENP on cellular data. P400s don't come with cellular data. 

How to switch ENP to Cellular Data? :  settings (Air & Saturn) ->network & Internet -> cellular data -> check to see if it says active -> press the back arrow , go to WiFi and turn it off. If the cellular data doesn't start once you do, that simple power cycle of the ENP should connect you to 4G/5G network depending on your region.

How to rectify EOD Standalone transactions(a.k.a missing transactions on Pos system (Till))? :  Have customers mark it down as a miscellaneous  product or misc product, which is located at the bottom of the basket on the right hand side with Plus sign -> hit plus sign again on the left hand sign & enter the information needed-> pay-> Epos Now standalone or standalone ( it will record it like a cash transaction and not a card transaction customer will not be charged again.)

Note: If a customer doesn't record those standalone transactions, through the till app. Customers will have to wait till they receive their payouts and visit -> reporting -> payments -> payments payout in the back office to view that information or customer can request for the standalone transactions through Epos now staff, where we can give a transaction list of the ENP, but customer must provide the full serial number of the device. Located on the back of the terminal. 

If you have a PDQ machine from a third party, please reach out to your merchant provider, as epos now doesn't hold records of non-ENP customers.

