-> ENP Unresponsive/ COG (sub category)
Troubleshooting Steps
Config :settings (P400 9*green )-> configuration -> code: 0779 -> reset device .

Software Version Update: Settings (P400 9*green )-> device Info->  software version updates -> update if available.

Hard Rest: Turn the device over, till you see the back of the device. -> put your thumbs on the back of the lid, and pull towards you. -> it pops back a little, and lift the lid up. -> take the battery out, and time it for 2 minutes before putting the battery back in. ( Depending on the device, if you have a Saturn ( F1S2), there will be a  clamp on the  left hand side of the battery, pinch it towards the battery and it will fall out; if you have an Air (AMS1) just gently tap it on your hand.)

Power Cycle: for p400 unplug it from the power source (outlet/ power point/ power socket/  wall socket/ main socket/ plug socket). Saturn press the power button on the left hand side. Air press the power button on the right hand side.

Network:  (P400 9* green) settings-> network and Internet -> wifi or cellular data (cellular data is only for Air & Saturn)  P400 can only be connected via of ethernet or wifi. If you are connected via wifi make sure  the cable isn't damaged or try replacing it. P400 struggle with wifi, it's best to keep them on ethernet. If you enable cellular data, please make sure to connect to some sort of Wi-Fi/ hotspot to connect to the cellular data, as you will need a network to activate it, if you haven't already. Once you go to cellular data as long as it says active, your enp is connected to cellular data.  You will see this with towers in the upper right hand corner. If you don't see it at first, do a power cycle.

 
