-> Printer Error / Setup/ Order utilities (sub category)
Troubleshooting Steps

Order utilities has been discontinued for windows devices 
Common Error for Order Utilities: It stops working or it gets flooded with printing inquiries. Pull screen down in upper right hand corner, pull down the first box again -> bottom right corner it be a gear (⚙️)  next to a pencil, select the gear-> apps & notifications -> Order Utilities-> storage -> Clear data -> scroll up from bottom of the screen -> hit the circle 🔴 button -> order utilities -> press start -> press Play (Start) ▶️ 

Check behind the printer is connected properly to Ethernet to tower, if you're doing Ethernet ( make sure cable is in correct port. The Cashdrawer port is smaller than the Ethernet port. cashdrawer cable is flat, not Ethernet cable and is hardware into cashdrawer). There is USB B to USB A cable connector. Where you plug the USB B ( = ) connector into the till and the USB A ( [ ] ) connector to the  printer .
If you're doing Ethernet and if your till haven't picked up the printer. To do a test print -> turn off the printer -> put your thumb on the feed button -> turn on the printer -> hold feed button for 2 sec -> take your thumb off the feed button. It should print you a long sheet of paper. Look for on the sheet of paper,  for the word protocol , then look for IP address, under Mac address. If the IP address states, “ 192.168.123.100,”  that means its static IP address and your printer is off line. Reboot your network tower and try again. If you get a fee dump paper, don't do feed dump try again.  There is also a possibility that you have gotten the printer setup confused, and have the printer on a USB connection. 

We have our Epos now printer Pos80gx, we have third party printers we integrate with bixolon 220dx , Star printer (which has two versions Bluetooth and Ethernet/ USB printer.) ,  Epson printer, & Bixolon Label printer. Epos now only integrate these printers and have the drivers to supply to customers. We will not be able to set-up any other third party printers outside of Epos Now and third party partnerships we have. Windows may have more leeway, however, no guarantee it will work, and you as the customer will have to reach out to a third party vendor of the printer or buy a printer form Epos Now, so you have Warranty on the printers, if purchased through Epos Now.

To setup receipt printer: 3 lines->  settings -> peripherals-> setup receipt printer-> follow the step provided by the pos system, to complete the setup process.( This is for Androids, POS systems & Saturns.)


To setup order printer: 3 lines->  settings -> peripherals-> setup order printer-> follow the step provided by the pos system, to complete the setup process. ( This is for Androids, POS systems & Saturns.)

To setup Bixolon Label( On Pos System): It is plug in and play. How to use it? Back office -> manage-> products -> advance (Depending on product list your on it be a button on left hand side that will say advance or  it be on the right hand side, press the 3 dots & then select advance edit.) -> Generate Labels. This is where you can generate labels. Highly advised for customers to play around with the generate labels page to customize to your preferences. 

For Windows devices to set up the printer on your Windows devices, please download the driver provided by the agent. After downloading the file. Go to File Explorer ->  go to downloads or  the designated folder you have saved it to-> extract all-> windows settings ->  printers & devices -> add printer or search it in the search engine. You can also locate these settings options in the control panel or your printer & device folder.

To set up USB to Windows: select local -> search for printer -> select add printer driver, go to  the file folder of the printer -> select printer driver ( If Epos Now, the driver is called Zling.)-> don't share the printer, keep it private -> name the printer.  Next-> right click printer or click printer, and select manage -> go to printer properties -> Port -> enable printer pooling -> select virtual ports and LTP1. Test print printer.  Next -> go to Epos now app ( login to register if you're not already) -> 3 lines->  settings -> peripherals-> App settings -> Receipt printer & select the printer you want to print your receipts.

To set up Ethernet to Windows: select TCP/ IP -> Enter IP address -> search for printer -> select add printer driver, go to  the file folder of the printer -> select printer driver ( If Epos Now, the driver is called Zling.)-> don't share the printer, keep it private -> name the printer. Test print printer.  Next -> go to Epos now app ( login to register if you're not already) -> 3 lines->  settings -> peripherals-> App settings -> offline/online order printer -> select what order preference you want ( order A, order B, Kitchen, front, rear, & bar) & select the printer you want to print your order printer.

Note: If you are going to do order printing, please ensure your categories are set up with correct printer preferences, to do that go to back office -> manage -> categories ->  under column “ order/ lay away", select your order printing preferences. This option will be presented during setup through the till app on Android device/ POS system, however for Windows users, please go to the back office.

Built in printer common error: printer is not printing, to rectify this issue go to 3 lines->  settings -> peripherals-> setup receipt printer-> got to your printer that's already saved in the system, which is 1.1.1.1 ( built in printer) -> hit the three dots and delete the printer. Power off the till (restart is also an option). Power button located on bottom right hand side. Power back on the till. Next go back into peripherals to set up the receipt  printer again ( 3 lines->  settings -> peripherals-> setup receipt printer-> follow the pos system instructions to re-add  the receipt printer.). The reason the built in printer is not printing is due to the fact that the firmware of the printer got stuck installing during the first setup of the printer.  

If order printer gets disconnected check to see if the order printer is disconnected via of Ethernet ( see if the light is still flashing where the Ethernet cable is plugged in at, if it's not flashing it could be disconnected via of Ethernet or cable has been damaged/ gone bad.) or the printer has been unplugged. This goes for Windows and Androids devices. Also, reboot network tower, if you are unable to do so, contact your network provider as  they can assist with IP address issues.  

How to change Ip address of printer: Warning ⚠️ before proceeding you must have your previous network provider to do this if not. Reach out to your new provider and change your gateway to the original printer's gateway. So, say if your IP address was originally for printer 192.168.4.80, your gateway number would be 4 and it will fix your printer's connectivity issue. Or buy a new printer through Epos Now ( if the printer is still in warranty, then swap it for a new printer.) .

Steps to changing printer IP address. Open up your web browser ( chrome, Firefox, edge or Opera.) ->  type in the IP Address of your printer, for example: “ 192. 168.4.80.” ->  enter -> TCP/ IP Settings or  Configuration settings -> go to IP address and type in the new free IP address given by the POS system to locate the free IP address. Go to network diagnostics -> IP scanner -> at the top it shows a free IP address.  If your till is a windows device it is best to reach out to your network provider to do this for you. If you don't feel comfortable changing IP addresses on your own, contact your network provider. Lastly, reboot the printer. 

How to calibrate Bixolon Label Printer?   Press and hold the feed button, till the light  flashes yellow & red, then green -> then press the feed button again -> test print the printer. Or  set-up the Bixolon printer to your computer, where you have more customization in font sizes. To set up a label printer ( On Windows ) -> download the file given to you by the agent -> open  installation and start the install process -> follow the prompt-> test print the printer. (Please make sure the printer was already plugged into the windows devices.)

If the printer isn't printing properly it is a swap or a new hardware purchase. 

Epos Now printers are Thermal printers, buy thermal paper through Epos Now.

Apple devices have cloud sync and printer setup issues, due to the terms of IOS  data protection protocol. May not be compatible with Epos Now devices and partnerships.

Paper Issue -> make sure the paper is counter clock wise, and not clock wise, over the roller, not under the roller. Make sure paper is sticking out a little and the printer will readjust itself.

Built- in printer blade error -> open the printer door ( leaver on the right hand side pop it towards you.)-> lay till onto it's back -> there will be half hexagon hole, on the top of under the screen of the till-> stick your finger in there, and pop it open -> there will be a white gear, spin it  counter clock wise 3 times, and try close printer door. Warning ⚠️ - Don't do it to much or it can get sucked up into the machine  or spin it down to much or the blade will fall out. If either of these happen, the printer blade can't be taken out or falls out; it can't be put back in. You will have to swap it for the till or if you're out of warranty, you will have to buy a new till or printer. 

Note: If you're having issues removing a printer, go to your window’s search engine and type in print management -> go to printers-> right click -> cancel jobs-> right click again, and delete printer.

Epos Now printers are Thermal printers, buy thermal paper through Epos Now.

Apple devices have cloud sync and printer setup issues, due to the terms of IOS  data protection protocol. May not be compatible with Epos Now devices and partnerships.

Paper Issue -> make sure the paper is counter clock wise, and not clock wise, over the roller, not under the roller. Make sure paper is sticking out a little and the printer will readjust itself.

Built- in printer blade error -> open the printer door ( leaver on the right hand side pop it towards you.)-> lay till onto it's back -> there will be half hexagon hole, on the top of under the screen of the till-> stick your finger in there, and pop it open -> there will be a white gear, spin it  counter clock wise 3 times, and try close printer door. Warning ⚠️ - Don't do it to much or it can get sucked up into the machine  or spin it down to much or the blade will fall out. If either of these happen, the printer blade can't be taken out or falls out; it can't be put back in. You will have to swap it for the till or if you're out of warranty, you will have to buy a new till or printer. 

Note: If you're having issues removing a printer, go to your window’s search engine and type in print management -> go to printers-> right click -> cancel jobs-> right click again, and delete printer.




-> CashDrawer Error (sub category)
Troubleshooting Steps
Make sure the cash drawer is not plugged into the Ethernet port or it won't pop.

 Cash drawer plugged in, but still won't pop: to rectify this issue go to 3 lines->  settings -> peripherals-> setup receipt printer-> got to your printer that's already saved in the system, which is 1.1.1.1 ( built in printer or USB printer [Doesn't have IP Address]) -> hit the three dots and delete the printer. Add it in again, by following the pos system instructions to set it up. If the cash drawer isn't popping on the Pos System, it is due to the printer cutting off services to the cashdrawer. It's a simple fix. By removing and adding the printer back in 

If the cash drawer won't pop on windows device: go into your windows settings ->printer & devices -> go to your receipt printer, and click it or right click -> manage-> printer properties → printer settings -> go to cash drawer, and change it from after print receipts to before it prints receipts, you can also change it to 2 after receipts, as well 

If the trouble shooting steps doesn't work, then it is a swap( swap it , will only be tailor to that serial number of the device giving error.) or a purchase of a printer and cash drawer, as we have no full certainty if it's the printer or cash drawer that's unresponsive or upgrade your till to a Built-in printer Pos system.

