Troubleshooting Steps
Question: What device do you have: Windows, Tablet, Mac,  POS System (Till) or Saturn (ENP)?
Unassigned the license to do a force cloud sync -> back office -> setup -> locations -> devices -> Unassign license.


Windows: 
Option 1: clear temp files: use Windows search icon / press Windows icon type in run/ hot key Win+ R-> %temp% ( enter) -> clear all files .( Make sure to permanently delete & restart the till)
Option 2:  update till app, by going to out back office -> till-> download.->  go into search type(or look  on your left hand side apps that's available and select settings.)settings -> press apps and notifications -> look for Epos Now Till -> uninstall it-> search engine -> File explorer -> downloads -> open newly installed app and install. ( Customers will not have to worry about re-setting up or login; it will already have them login.)
Option 3: clear data,  file explorer -> press desktop → your local driver ( C: or Epos Now)-> Program files / Program files (86)[ depending where file was saved.] -> Right click and rename EposNow to EposNow.old. (if you can't see it  enabled  program Data: -> go to view-> show-> hidden items on file explorer.)
Additional information: if your app isn't up to date which is 3.4.1.4 or 3.4.1.7( given from staff) please update your software version. Note:  Epos Now no longer supports Windows devices & Mac os devices. No more updates. Let's talk about upgrading your devices before the hard drive is unable to clear temp files anymore, which will bring down your system permanently.

Tablets: Install and reinstall Epos Now Till app and reset up your information( you don't have to re-setup back office information, just hardware information to tablet.)

POS System (Till):

Pull screen down in upper right hand corner, pull down the first box again -> bottom right corner it be a gear (⚙️)  next to a pencil, select the gear-> apps & notifications -> Epos Now Till-> storage -> Clear data -> got back to the till and reset up device and log back into the back office, select store, device and business as usual.

Pull screen down in upper right hand corner, pull down the first box again -> bottom right corner it be a gear (⚙️)  next to a pencil, select the gear-> network & Internet-> Wi-Fi-> select network-> put in network password or connect it via of Ethernet.

Check for updates: press the back arrow till your on main screen of settings again -> scroll to bottom till you see system -> select system ->  system updates -> go to apps -> look for Epos Now -> Look see  if it say Update or Up to Date, if it needs to be updated, select update.  Anything that's below 1.1.107+ is out of date and should be updated to the latest software version.



