Back Office (Main Category)
-> Stock (sub category)
Troubleshooting Steps
How to add stock to a product: Back office -> manage-> products -> advance (Depending on product list your on it be a button on left hand side that will say advance or  it be on the right hand side, press the 3 dots & then select advance edit.) -> scroll all the way down till you see stock adjust and add your stock there or when you first make the product, add the stock information, it's more clear if you do it under Quick Add, buy turning on stock level toggle or do bulk import app you can purchase from us, get 30 day free trial. Can uninstall to cancel subscription at any time.

How to Update stock: back office -> stock management -> press stock adjust ( double tap if you're on Android or POS system or double click, that will open up the box line, where you update the stock. It is based on whatever location you set your products under for stock, so keep that in mind if you have multiple store locations. You can also customize the columns by hitting columns. Filter allows you to work on certain things, such as categories, and you can work on that whole entire stock inventory for one category.)

Stock order: is only shared between store locations under one back office account can't happen outside of your back office. To do it  back office -> stock -> stock order ( this is where you can create stock order or receive and mark it as received, etc.)

Track Stock:  back office-> reporting -> stock( you have 3 options, if you want to view your stock levels go to stock level. If you want to view stock changes, go to stock changes. Each one is pretty explanatory.)

Can you get notifications about your stock dropping? Yes, just make sure when set up stock you select a stock alert. Which will alert you via of email. Or set-up a dashboard to do that: go to the dashboard , create it and select what you want to receive via of email, under reporting. Once you have done that, in reporting ->  schedule emails and create a schedule email for time and date where it issues out to you a report, just make sure you attach your dashboard you created earlier today.

Use Bulk import application, it's a 30 day free trial and can cancel any time after that. Depending on the region, prices may vary.

How to use Bulk Import: Back office -> app store -> my apps -> setup. Download the stock sheet and update your stock using Excel or Google sheets. You can use any of these templates to your specified need. How to upload the CSV file(must be CSV, and it must be files that come to back office bulk import, no outside or home made templates.) -> upload your modified template -> download -> Import.

